{"data": {"id": "4104670", "type": "fullArticle", "attributes": {"publishOn": "2017-09-06T22:07:14-04:00", "isLockedPro": false, "commentCount": 10, "gettyImageUrl": null, "videoPreviewUrl": null, "videoDuration": null, "themes": {"reality-seeker": {"id": 573645, "slug": "reality-seeker", "kind": "common", "non_theme": true}, "investing-ideas": {"id": 10727, "slug": "investing-ideas", "kind": "general", "path": "/stock-ideas", "title": "Stock Ideas", "sasource": "theme_breadcrumb"}, "long-ideas": {"id": 1936, "slug": "long-ideas", "kind": "breadcrumb", "path": "/stock-ideas/long-ideas", "title": "Long Ideas", "sasource": "theme_breadcrumb"}, "has": {"id": 4040, "slug": "has", "kind": "common", "non_theme": true}, "consumer-goods": {"id": 17829, "slug": "consumer-goods", "kind": "common", "path": "/stock-ideas/consumer-goods", "title": "Consumer\u00a0", "non_theme": true}, "sa-exclusive": {"id": 17335, "slug": "sa-exclusive", "kind": "general"}, "premium-base-payment": {"id": 162415, "slug": "premium-base-payment", "kind": "general"}, "us": {"id": 326, "slug": "us", "kind": "common", "non_theme": true}, "toys-games": {"id": 17860, "slug": "toys-games", "kind": "common", "non_theme": true}, "consumer-discretionary": {"id": 25, "slug": "consumer-discretionary", "kind": "sector", "path": "/stock-ideas/consumer-goods", "title": "Consumer\u00a0", "sasource": "theme_breadcrumb"}}, "title": "Hasbro's Advance Has No End In Sight", "summary": ["Hasbro still has strong growth potential.", "Management showed exceptional capital management skills.", "The strong potential of the firm is not priced in by the market yet."], "structuredInsights": null, "isPaywalled": false, "lastModified": "2017-09-06T22:07:14-04:00", "isModerated": false, "closestTradingDate": "2017-09-07", "beforeOpeningHours": false, "isEarningsSlides": false, "isExclusive": true, "isTranscript": false, "excludedByTag": false, "transcriptPath": null, "likesCount": 0, "disabledStatus": "allowed", "disabledMessage": null, "status": "published", "disclosure": "<p id=\"a-disclosure\"><b>Analyst\u2019s Disclosure:</b> <span>I am/we are long HAS.</span> <span id=\"top-business-disclosure\"> I wrote this article myself, and it expresses my own opinions. I am not receiving compensation for it (other than from Seeking Alpha). I have no business relationship with any company whose stock is mentioned in this article. </span></p><p id='a-disclosure-more'><strong>Seeking Alpha's Disclosure:</strong> Past performance is no guarantee of future results. No recommendation or advice is being given as to whether any investment is suitable for a particular investor. Any views or opinions expressed above may not reflect those of Seeking Alpha as a whole. Seeking Alpha is not a licensed securities dealer, broker or US investment adviser or investment bank. Our analysts are third party authors that include both professional investors and individual investors who may not be licensed or certified by any institute or regulatory body.</p>", "articleActionableItem": null, "inEmbargo": false, "isNoindex": false, "isNoarchive": true, "content": "<p>As the licensed toy manufacturer for the Star Wars, Marvel and Disney (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/DIS\" title=\"The Walt Disney Company\">DIS</a>) movies, Hasbro (NASDAQ: <span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/HAS\" title=\"Hasbro, Inc.\">HAS</a></span>) has strong growth potential as related movies will consistently be produced until 2020. The firm has dominated the toy manufacturer industry, and we believe that the recent selloff has offered investors a great opportunity to purchase the stock at a reasonable price level to capture the growth of the stock.</p> <h3>Triumph over Mattel</h3> <p>Stock price performance comparison of two companies:</p> <p><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2017/9/48251972_15044973140305_rId4_thumb.jpg\" data-width=\"640\" data-height=\"325\" data-og-image-twitter_small_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_large_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_image_post=\"true\" data-og-image-msn=\"true\" data-og-image-facebook=\"true\" data-og-image-google_news=\"true\" data-og-image-google_plus=\"true\" data-og-image-linkdin=\"true\" fetchpriority=\"high\"></p> <p>(<a href=\"https://www.tradingview.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">TradingView</a>)</p> <p>There are now two toy manufacturers that hold significant market share in the industry, Hasbro and Mattel (NASDAQ: <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/MAT\" title=\"Mattel, Inc.\">MAT</a>). The major difference between the two firms are their toy brands and licensing. Hasbro develops toys and games for partners such as Marvel and Disney, which include popular theatrical releases such as Captain America and Star Wars, therefore enjoying rapid growth. On the contrary, Mattel owns brands with less growth catalyst such as UNO and Barbie and the firm as a whole shows little strength of growth. The market has recognized the two firm's difference, sending the stock of Hasbro up 18.9% while Mattel is down by -49.91% in the past year.</p> <p><span><a href=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2017/9/6/48251972-1504732722352475_origin.png\" rel=\"lightbox\" data-width=\"1234\" data-height=\"726\" data-og-image-twitter_small_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_large_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_image_post=\"true\" data-og-image-msn=\"true\" data-og-image-facebook=\"true\" data-og-image-google_news=\"true\" data-og-image-google_plus=\"true\" data-og-image-linkdin=\"true\"><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2017/9/6/48251972-1504732722352475.png\" data-width=\"640\" data-height=\"377\" data-og-image-twitter_small_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_large_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_image_post=\"true\" data-og-image-msn=\"true\" data-og-image-facebook=\"true\" data-og-image-google_news=\"true\" data-og-image-google_plus=\"true\" data-og-image-linkdin=\"true\" loading=\"lazy\"></a></span></p> <p><span><a href=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2017/9/6/48251972-1504732850087911_origin.png\" rel=\"lightbox\" data-width=\"1229\" data-height=\"715\" data-og-image-twitter_small_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_large_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_image_post=\"true\" data-og-image-msn=\"true\" data-og-image-facebook=\"true\" data-og-image-google_news=\"true\" data-og-image-google_plus=\"true\" data-og-image-linkdin=\"true\"><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2017/9/6/48251972-1504732850087911.png\" data-width=\"640\" data-height=\"372\" data-og-image-twitter_small_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_large_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_image_post=\"true\" data-og-image-msn=\"true\" data-og-image-facebook=\"true\" data-og-image-google_news=\"true\" data-og-image-google_plus=\"true\" data-og-image-linkdin=\"true\" loading=\"lazy\"></a></span></p> <p>The difference in growth of the two firms is obvious by comparing their revenue. At the end of 2016, Hasbro's revenue has increased by 22.7% compared to that of 2012, on the contrary, at the end of 2016, Mattel's revenue has decreased by 15% when compared to that of 2012.</p> <h3>Financial</h3> <p><strong>Income statement</strong></p> <p>Q2 Segment revenue breakdown</p> <p><span><a href=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2017/9/48251972_15044973140305_rId6.png\" rel=\"lightbox\" data-width=\"1430\" data-height=\"203\" data-og-image-twitter_small_card=\"false\" data-og-image-twitter_large_card=\"false\" data-og-image-twitter_image_post=\"false\" data-og-image-msn=\"false\" data-og-image-facebook=\"false\" data-og-image-google_news=\"false\" data-og-image-google_plus=\"false\" data-og-image-linkdin=\"false\"><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2017/9/48251972_15044973140305_rId6_thumb.jpg\" data-width=\"640\" data-height=\"91\" data-og-image-twitter_small_card=\"false\" data-og-image-twitter_large_card=\"false\" data-og-image-twitter_image_post=\"false\" data-og-image-msn=\"false\" data-og-image-facebook=\"false\" data-og-image-google_news=\"false\" data-og-image-google_plus=\"false\" data-og-image-linkdin=\"false\" loading=\"lazy\"></a></span></p> <p>Hasbro is obviously doing great in recent years, benefitted by the reproduction of the Star Wars series and <a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/features/2015-disney-princess-hasbro/\" rel=\"nofollow\">the deal</a> with Disney (NYSE: <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/DIS\" title=\"The Walt Disney Company\">DIS</a>) to manufacture Disney princess dolls in 2016. As shown in the revenue breakdown, franchise brand is the fastest-growing segment of all segments.</p> <p>Hasbro's revenue by quarter:</p> <p><img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/uploads/2017/9/48251972_15044973140305_rId5_thumb.jpg\" data-width=\"640\" data-height=\"376\" data-og-image-twitter_small_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_large_card=\"true\" data-og-image-twitter_image_post=\"true\" data-og-image-msn=\"true\" data-og-image-facebook=\"true\" data-og-image-google_news=\"true\" data-og-image-google_plus=\"true\" data-og-image-linkdin=\"true\" loading=\"lazy\"></p> <p>(Company Filings)</p> <p>Revenue consistently</p>", "twitContent": "$HAS - Hasbro's Advance Has No End In Sight. https://seekingalpha.com/article/4104670-hasbros-advance-no-end-in-sight?source=tweet ", "innerMarketing": null, "marketingBullet": "", "isMpwLocked": true, "isReit": false, "videoData": null, "marketingBulletVariant": null, "marketingBio": null, "audioDuration": null}, "relationships": {"author": {"data": {"id": "102939", "type": "author"}}, "sentiments": {"data": []}, "primaryTickers": {"data": [{"id": "4040", "type": "tag"}]}, "secondaryTickers": {"data": []}, "otherTags": {"data": [{"id": "573645", "type": "tag"}, {"id": "1936", "type": "tag"}, {"id": "17829", "type": "tag"}, {"id": "17335", "type": "tag"}, {"id": "162415", "type": "tag"}, {"id": "10727", "type": "tag"}, {"id": "326"